summary: STOREKEEPER II with over 10 years of experience in procurement, inventory control, vendor relations, and customer service. Proficient in using PeopleSoft for procurements and shipments, Excel reporting, inventory cycle counts, and fleet service parts. Skilled in problem solving, communication, leadership, and forklift safety training. Experienced in handling shipments, order fulfillment, and liaison with government and departmental personnel.

experience.title: Storekeeper II
experience.description: Maintained and reconciled inventory through clerical support; used PeopleSoft to procure and receive shipments obtained by purchase order. Created Excel spreadsheets for reports; managed inventory files and researched inventory problems. Conducted inventory cycle counts; coordinated stock and documented transactions. Provided Customer Service to Departmental and Fleet Maintenance Personnel; processed work orders and filled Fleet Purchase Requisitions; contacted vendors to procure fuel, parts and other automobile and truck supplies for fleet services. Trained forklift operator safety. Shipping: fulfilled orders with Infrared Scanning System (IFR). Operated forklift; used four-stage electronic single-person picker for order pulling and staging. Processed shipping orders for USPS, UPS, FedEx, and other carriers. Prepared overseas containers for shipment; verified quantities, shipment labels and paperwork.

experience.title: Warehouse Floor Supervisor
experience.description: Interviewed prospective employees for hire. Provided daily instruction to warehouse personnel and dispatched drivers for deliveries and pickups. Performed routine cycle counts to ensure inventory accuracy; verified proper stock placement. Received all incoming shipments; verified counts and created stock locations. Maintained inventory and quality control procedures.
